HEADWORD: Sept
<hw>Sept</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[A corruption of
<ets>sect</ets>, n.]</ety> <def>A clan, tribe, or family, proceeding
from a common progenitor; -- used especially of the ancient clans in
Ireland.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The chief, struck by the illustration, asked at once to be
baptized, and all his <qex>sept</qex> followed his example.</q>
<rj><qau>S. Lover.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Septaemia</ent>⟦br⟧
